NURS 3307 - Pharmacological Basis for Nursing
Pharmacotherapeutic aspects of nursing care are introduced and
supported by evidenced based findings to improve patient care.
Emphasis is on principles of safe administration of medications and
patient education for major drug classifications. The impact of
technology, economic, and regulatory forces as well as collaboration
with the health team are discussed. Ethical/legal and cultural
considerations are explored across the life span.
Prerequisite: Admission to the nursing program.
